[30;1m267 | [0m[35mwere changed to give sensible values. Previously, the ``flux`` value was[0m

[30;1m279 | [0m[35mImage-based PSF models are typically derived from observed data or from[0m
[30;1m280 | [0m[35mdetailed optical modeling. The PSF model can be a single PSF model for[0m
[30;1m281 | [0m[35mthe entire image or a grid of PSF models at fiducial detector positions,[0m

[30;1m54 | [0m[35m-------------------------[0m
[30;1m55 | [0m[35m[0m
[30;1m56 | [0m[35mFirst, we'll use the `~photutils.centroids.centroid_quadratic` function[0m
[30;1m57 | [0m[35mto find the source centroid from the simulated image defined above::[0m

[30;1m667 | [0m[35m[0m
[30;1m668 | [0m[35mAs mentioned in :ref:`creating-aperture-objects`, performing[0m
[30;1m669 | [0m[35mphotometry using apertures defined in sky coordinates simply requires[0m
[30;1m670 | [0m[35mdefining a "sky" aperture at positions defined by a[0m
[30;1m671 | [0m[35m:class:`~astropy.coordinates.SkyCoord` object.  Here we show an[0m
[30;1m672 | [0m[35mexample of photometry on real data using a[0m
[30;1m673 | [0m[35m`~photutils.aperture.SkyCircularAperture`.[0m

[31m--[ [0m[34mMatch #[0m[33m403[0m[34m of [0m[33m689[0m[31m ]--[0m
   Rule Id: [34mBD000600[0m
       Tag: [34mSecurity.Backdoor.LOLBAS.Windows[0m

[30;1m1 | [0m[35mPixel Coordinate Conventions[0m
[30;1m2 | [0m[35m============================[0m
[30;1m3 | [0m[35m[0m
[30;1m4 | [0m[35mIn Photutils, integer pixel coordinates are located at the center of[0m
[30;1m5 | [0m[35mpixels, and they are 0-indexed, matching the Python 0-based indexing.[0m
[30;1m6 | [0m[35mThat means the first pixel is considered pixel ``0``, but pixel[0m
[30;1m7 | [0m[35mcoordinate ``0`` is the *center* of that pixel. Hence, the first pixel[0m
